        {
          "scid": "an5.16:1.1",
          "pli": "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, balāni. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, there are these five powers. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.16:1.2",
          "pli": "Katamāni pañca? ",
          "en": "What five? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.16:1.3",
          "pli": "Saddhābalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, satibalaṃ, samādhibalaṃ, paññābalaṃ—",
          "en": "The powers of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.16:1.4",
          "pli": "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca balāni. ",
          "en": "These are the five powers. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.16:1.5",
          "pli": "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ balānaṃ etaṃ aggaṃ etaṃ saṅgāhikaṃ etaṃ saṅghātaniyaṃ, yadidaṃ paññābalaṃ. ",
          "en": "Of these five powers, the power of wisdom is the chief. It holds and binds everything together. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.16:1.6",
          "pli": "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kūṭāgārassa etaṃ aggaṃ etaṃ saṅgāhikaṃ etaṃ saṅghātaniyaṃ, yadidaṃ kūṭaṃ. ",
          "en": "It’s like a bungalow. The roof-peak is the chief point, which holds and binds everything together. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.16:1.7",
          "pli": "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ balānaṃ etaṃ aggaṃ etaṃ saṅgāhikaṃ etaṃ saṅghātaniyaṃ, yadidaṃ paññābalan”ti. ",
          "en": "In the same way, of these five powers, the power of wisdom is the chief. It holds and binds everything together.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.16:1.8",
          "pli": "Chaṭṭhaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
